The paper discusses the problem of world modeling for robots in indoor environments, which is a common topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves clustering objects based on their attributes, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a dependent Dirichlet process mixture model, which is a probabilistic modeling technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
